# import data Fashion-MNIST
from keras.datasets import fashion_mnist
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = fashion_mnist.load_data()

# normalization
x_train = x_train / 255.0
x_test = x_test / 255.0

# reshape
x_train = x_train.reshape(-1,28,28,1)
x_test = x_test.reshape(-1,28,28,1)

In [ ]:
fmnist_start = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', activation='relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

fmnist_start.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/one-layer start/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
history_start = fmnist_start.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                                validation_split=0.2,
                                callbacks=myCallbacks)

plt.figure(figsize=(18,5))
epoch = [i for i in range(1,101)]
plt.subplot(1,2,1)

plt.title('accuracy')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()

plt.subplot(1,2,2)
plt.plot(epoch, history_start.history['loss'], label='training loss')
plt.plot(epoch, history_start.history['val_loss'], label='validation loss')
plt.title('loss')
plt.grid()

plt.show()

From picture "loss", we can see that there is overfitting.

Do regularization

  • maxpooling
  • dropout
  • BN
  • weight dacay
In [ ]:
# add maxpooling

modelA = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', activation='relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),

        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

modelA.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/maxpool/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
historyA = modelA.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2,
                      callbacks=myCallbacks)

In [ ]:
# add dropout
modelB = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', activation='relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

modelB.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/dropout/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
historyB = modelB.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2,
                      callbacks=myCallbacks)

# add another dropout layer
modelC = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', activation='relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

modelC.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/2 dropout/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
historyC = modelC.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2,
                      callbacks=myCallbacks)

# add weight decay

from keras.regularizers import l2

modelD = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)),
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

modelD.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/weight decay 0.001/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
historyD = modelD.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2,
                      callbacks=myCallbacks)

        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

modelE.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

#myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/weight decay 0.01/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
historyE = modelE.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2)
                      #callbacks=myCallbacks)

# add batch normalization
modelF = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

modelF.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

#myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/weight decay 0.01/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
historyF = modelF.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2)
                      #callbacks=myCallbacks)

In [ ]:
# filter=16
filter16 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

filter16.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

#myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/weight decay 0.01/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
history_filter16 = filter16.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2)
                      #callbacks=myCallbacks)

# filter=64
filter64 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

filter64.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

#myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/weight decay 0.01/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
history_filter64 = filter64.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2)
                      #callbacks=myCallbacks)

# kernel size=(3,3)
kernel3 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(3,3), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

kernel3.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

#myCallbacks = [tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir="logs/weight decay 0.01/", histogram_freq=1)]
               
history_kernel3 = kernel3.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2)
                      #callbacks=myCallbacks)

# optimizer='sgd'
sgd = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

sgd.compile(optimizer='sgd',
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

               
history_sgd = sgd.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2)

RMSprop = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

                      validation_split=0.2)

# learning rate=0.001
adam_lr1 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

adam_lr1.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

               
history_lr1 = adam_lr1.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2)

# learning rate=0.0001
adam_lr2 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

adam_lr2.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.0001),
               loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

               
history_lr2 = adam_lr2.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                      validation_split=0.2)

from tensorflow.keras import initializers
In [ ]:
# random normal, mean=0, std=0.01
kerIni_norm_1 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5),
                               kernel_initializer=initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0.0, stddev=0.01)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])


kerIni_norm_1.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
                      loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                      metrics=['accuracy'])
               
history_norm1 = kerIni_norm_1.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                                validation_split=0.2)

        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

                      loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                      metrics=['accuracy'])

                                validation_split=0.2)

# random uniform, min=0, max=1
kerIni_uni_1 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5),
                               kernel_initializer=initializers.RandomUniform(minval=0., maxval=1.)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

kerIni_uni_1.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
                      loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                      metrics=['accuracy'])

                                validation_split=0.2)

# random uniform, min=-0.5, max=0.5
kerIni_uni_2 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5),
                               kernel_initializer=initializers.RandomUniform(minval=-0.5, maxval=0.5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

kerIni_uni_2.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
                      loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                      metrics=['accuracy'])
               
history_uni2 = kerIni_uni_2.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                                validation_split=0.2)

In [ ]:
# add one convolutional layer
twocnnA = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

twocnnA.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
                loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                metrics=['accuracy'])
               
history_twocnnA = twocnnA.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                                validation_split=0.2)

In [ ]:
twocnnB = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

twocnnB.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
                loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                metrics=['accuracy'])
               
history_twocnnB = twocnnB.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                                validation_split=0.2)

# compare two layer cnn with different structures
plt.figure(figsize=(18,5))
epoch = [i for i in range(1,101)]
plt.subplot(1,2,1)
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnA.history['val_accuracy'], label='structure 1')
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnB.history['val_accuracy'], label='structure 2')
plt.title('accuracy')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()

plt.subplot(1,2,2)
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnA.history['val_loss'], label='structure 1')
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnB.history['val_loss'], label='structure 2')
plt.title('loss')
plt.grid()
plt.legend()
plt.show()

the second structure is better. since there is no overfitting, we double dense units

In [ ]:
twocnnC = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(256, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

twocnnC.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
                loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                metrics=['accuracy'])

                                validation_split=0.2)

# compare two layer cnn with different structures
plt.figure(figsize=(18,5))
epoch = [i for i in range(1,101)]
plt.subplot(1,2,1)
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnB.history['val_accuracy'], label='128 hidden units')
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnC.history['val_accuracy'], label='256 hidden units')
plt.title('accuracy')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()

plt.subplot(1,2,2)
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnB.history['val_loss'], label='128 hidden units')
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnC.history['val_loss'], label='256 hidden units')
plt.title('loss')
plt.grid()
plt.legend()
plt.show()

256 hidden units has better performance

since we have achieved desired accuracy, we directly try 4 layer cnn to see the results

In [ ]:
twocnnD = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(256, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

twocnnD.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
                loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                metrics=['accuracy'])
               
history_twocnnD = twocnnD.fit(x_train, y_train, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                                validation_split=0.2)

since filter=32 has higher accuracy, we think it is our best model.

try data augmentation

In [ ]:
# try three data augmentation methods
# 1. filp up and down
# 2. filp right and left
# 3. 

def dataAug1(image):
  image_output = tf.image.random_flip_up_down(image, seed=0)
  return image_output

def dataAug2(image):
  image_output = tf.image.random_flip_left_right(image, seed=0)
  return image_output

def dataAug3(image):
  image_output = tf.image.adjust_contrast(image, 1.5)
  return image_output

aug_data = np.zeros([60000,28,28,1])
for i in range(60000):
  if i<20000:
    aug_data[i] = dataAug1(x_train[i])
  elif 20000<=i<40000:
    aug_data[i] = dataAug2(x_train[i])
  else:
    aug_data[i] = dataAug3(x_train[i])

train_aug = np.concatenate((x_train, aug_data))
label_aug = np.concatenate((y_train, y_train))

train_aug.shape, label_aug.shape
Out[ ]:
((120000, 28, 28, 1), (120000,))
In [ ]:
aug = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
                                     
        tf.keras.layers.Input((28,28,1)),
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(5,5), padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(1e-5)),
        tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
        tf.keras.layers.Activation('relu'), 
        tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        
        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(256, 'relu'),
        tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, 'softmax')

])

aug.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
                loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                metrics=['accuracy'])
               
history_aug = aug.fit(train_aug, label_aug, batch_size=128, epochs=100,
                                validation_split=0.2)

plt.figure(figsize=(18,5))
epoch = [i for i in range(1,101)]
plt.subplot(1,2,1)
plt.plot(epoch, history_aug.history['accuracy'], label='training accuracy')
plt.plot(epoch, history_aug.history['val_accuracy'], label='validation accuracy')
plt.title('accuracy')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()

plt.subplot(1,2,2)
plt.plot(epoch, history_aug.history['loss'], label='training loss')
plt.plot(epoch, history_aug.history['val_loss'], label='validation loss')
plt.title('loss')
plt.grid()
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# compare whether or not use data augmentation
plt.figure(figsize=(18,5))
epoch = [i for i in range(1,101)]
plt.subplot(1,2,1)
plt.plot(epoch, history_aug.history['val_accuracy'], label='with augmentation')
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnD.history['val_accuracy'], label='without augmentation')
plt.title('accuracy')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()

plt.subplot(1,2,2)
plt.plot(epoch, history_aug.history['val_loss'], label='with augmentaton')
plt.plot(epoch, history_twocnnD.history['val_loss'], label='without augmentation')
plt.title('loss')
plt.grid()
plt.legend()
plt.show()
